{"000-section": {"000-title": "West Bengal Bina Mulya Samajik Suraksha Yojana 2020 [Free Social Security Scheme]"}, "001-section": {"000-title": "West Bengal govt. starts Bina Mulya Samajik Suraksha Yojana 2020, no premium for free social security scheme, 7.5 crore people to be benefited"}, "002-section": {"000-title": "WB Bina Mulya Samajik Suraksha Yojana", "001-normal": "The West Bengal Chief Minister Mamata Banerjee requested Finance Minister to include landless labourers as beneficiaries under Bina Mulya Samajik Suraksha Yojana (BMSS). Till date, there are 1.18 crore families which are enrolled under the Samajik Suraksha Yojana (SSY). The number will soon go upto 1.5 crore. In case there are 5 members in every family, the total number of beneficiaries would go upto 7.5 crore. All the poor people belonging to various unorganized sectors would be able to get Provident Fund (PF) and other benefits on attaining the age of 60 years.", "002-normal": "Poor people will have to pay single penny from their pockets. Previously, people needs to pay Rs. 25 per month while govt. used to contribute Rs. 30 for each beneficiary. The govt. has announced that there is no longer need to pay premium as govt. will bear entire cost. In case of death of beneficiaries, the family members would receive Rs. 2 lakh. In case someone gets disabled, each beneficiary will receive Rs. 1 lakh.", "003-normal": "CM has requested Finance and Labour dept. to make premium completely free as poor people belonging to unorganized sectors were facing difficulty in paying Rs. 25 per month. The CM also urges Finance Minister to bring landless labourers under Bina Mulya Samajik Suraksha Yojana."}, "003-section": {"000-title": "WB Jai Johar, Bandhu Prakalpa, Hasir Alo & Chai Sundari Schemes", "001-normal": "Various other schemes were also launched in West Bengal Budget 2020-2021:-", "002-listElement": "- **Hasir Alo** \u2013 In this scheme, around 35 lakh people would be able to avail free electricity in their house if the consumption is upto 75 units on quarterly basis. In case, the poor family uses an electrical lamp and fan prudently, then consumption will not exceed 75 units on quarterly basis. Rs. 200 crore has already been allocated for Hasir Alo Scheme.", "003-listElement": "- **Chaa Sundari** \u2013 This scheme will provide housing facilities to tea garden workers. Rs. 500 crore has been allocated for Chai Sundari Scheme.", "004-listElement": "- **Bandhu Prakalpa Scheme** \u2013 SC category people who are not receiving any pension from any agency will get Rs. 1,000 per month as pension. This pension would be given on attaining the age of 60 years.", "005-listElement": "- **Jai Johar Scheme** \u2013 ST category people who does not receive any pension from any agency will now get Rs. 1,000 per month as pension. The pension amount would be given on attaining the age of 60 years.", "006-normal": "The West Bengal govt. has also increased gratuity from Rs. 6 lakh to 123 lakh and home allowance from Rs. 6,000 to Rs. 12,000.", "007-normal": "Source / Reference Link: http://www.millenniumpost.in/kolkata/75-crore-people-will-reap-benefits-of-bina-mulya-samajik-suraksha-400703"}}